name: Chambre romantique avec accès à la cuisine
description: The bedroom is located in an apartment, on the garden floor, in a villa formed of three apartments, in the city center. The apartment is composed of 5 bedrooms. Rooms are rented on nocarz, as well as the entire or separate apartment into two apartments. My place is close to restaurants, family-friendly activities, nightlife, public transportation. Kitchen is available for tenants.

name: Cozy Furnished Loft in Geneva City Center
description: This charming loft beneath the eaves will undeniably make you fall in love with Geneva. Nested on the last floor of a 19th century building in the heart of the city, it is surrounded by 3 terraces overlooking the Jet d'eau (Geneva's most famous landmark). Its living room is equipped with a fireplace and high ceilings. The light-filled flat is rented with its elegant furniture and equipped kitchen and is a perfect place to enjoy Geneva all year long.
neighborhood_overview:
The loft is ideally located in the city center, in the lively Eaux Vives area. It is situated in a calm and charming street and is not noisy at all.
It has a bus stop, a tram stop, and a bike rental shop around the corner.

name: 4th charming room in Geneva
description: Our home is extremely charming, it's part of a 5 villas group that were all built during the year 1898, all located in a private and quiet road. The tram is 100 meters away from the house which makes it super easy to access the city center.
host_about: J'aime beaucoup la présence de visiteurs qui, s'ils choisissent ma maison, auront certainement du plaisir à y vivre et à y rencontrer d'autres voyageurs ou locataires à plus ou moins long terme. J'ai en tout  6 chambres à disposition dont une est déjà louée et deux sont pour moi. Beaucoup d'amis ou de clients passent au rez-de-chaussée et nous faisons parfois, hors-mis des séances de travail, aussi des diners et des fêtes, surtout en été. Si vous aimez le calme absolu vous ne devez pas choisir ce logement. Ici on aime la vie et on se régale!

name: Luminous Large Room in Apartment in Eaux-Vives
description:
In the heart of Geneva's Eaux Vives district, located in the business, restaurant and shopping area, the room is ideally placed at 5 minutes walk from the Jet d'Eau.

Direct access to commercial center of Eaux-Vives, and suitably close to all amenities (cinema, cafes, bars, public transport)

The renovated apartment is situated in a traditional apartment building

The area is very lively with many small restaurants and bars and is a fun place to go in the evenings

The accommodation is ideally located in the Servette district, northeast of Geneva, known for its multicultural and lively atmosphere. There are a wide variety of restaurants, shops and entertainment venues nearby.

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.

neighborhood_overview: This is the most diverse part of Geneva. Just like the Greenwich village in 1970's New York or Soho in London, the Pâquis quarter is one of Geneva's most colourful, and exciting neighbourhoods. A stones throw away from our doorstep is a tramstop offering connectivity to the rest of the city.

name: 011 Appartement centre-ville de Genève
neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

In addition, the neighborhood is very well connected by public transp
host_about: J'aime offrir une expérience de séjour personnalisée et authentique. Je partage mes connaissances locales pour aider les voyageurs à découvrir la ville comme un local. Mon objectif est de faire en sorte que mes voyageurs se sentent chez eux à Genève, en leur offrant un accueil chaleureux et toutes les informations pour un séjour inoubliable.

name: The Violet Room
description:
Hello, welcome to our Farmhouse in Geneva City Center, in La Servette. Super calm area, no road, no noise. Great Garden at disposal with barbecue, with tables and chairs, armchairs. And Hens.

Near all comodities. By foot, 15 min. to the City Center. Next to Bus 3, 9, 11, 22, Tram 14 and 18. 15 min. By Taxi, 15 min. to the Airport. Possibility to park a car, to be discussed.
host_about: Passionate about Geneva’s history, I like to tell stories for a good understanding of Geneva, an International City of only 199’000 inhabitants. The farmhouse was built in 1712, the very same year Jean-Jacques Rousseau, who was a philosopher, musician, botanist and novelist, was also born in Geneva. Apart from taking care of the guests, the house, the garden and the animals (cats, dog, hens), I am an entrepreneur and author. I write books on collaborative management, creativity, heutagogy and collective intelligence. My companion Cristobal is a “grand format” portrait’s painter. His studio is also located in the farmhouse. Our values : support, pleasure, integrity, creativity, listening, autonomy.

The residence is located in Collex-Bossy, a peaceful village offering a pleasant living environment, around 20 minutes' drive from Geneva. The ‘Collex , École’ bus stop is a 2-minute walk away, taking you to Geneva city centre in 30 minutes.

There are several restaurants in the village of Collex-Bossy. Supermarkets and other amenities can be found in neighbouring Versoix.

Cointrin international airport can be reached in 10 minutes by car or 30 minutes by public transport.

Things to see and do

- Bellevue or Versoix beaches
- Hiking in the Foretaille and Les Douves nature reserves
- Walking along the banks of Lake Geneva and the Jet d'eau
- Geneva Botanical Garden
- Palais des Nations
- Excursions on Lake Geneva

description: Spacious, bright, beautifully apartment (85sq meters /1bdr) in luxury building from 1890 with fireplace. Central location in Geneva. Very safe neighborhood. 1.2km walk to downtown train station. 12 minute bus ride from airport. Walking distance to lake (400m), grocery stores (20m), shops & restaurants. Direct bus to UN Palais, WTO, UNICEF, WMO, UNHCR, ITU, WIPO, GAVI, Campus Biotech, HUG Hospital Universitaire de  Genève, CICG Congress Centre.
neighborhood_overview: Centrally located, it is a residential neighborhood where you can find neighborhood restaurants, grocery stores, small cafés. There is a also Les Tilleuls Ateliers featuring art studios.
host_about: Originally from Canada, I've been living in Geneva since 2012 and working for the University Hospital Lausanne Foundation. Prior, I worked for an international NGO that conducts medical research on tropical diseases. I lead a team of fundraisers in Geneva, Tokyo, Rio, New York and Berlin responsible for in raising funds from governments and private donors such as the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation in Seattle.  I love my place, I  love living here and made a lot of new friends from around the world.  I'm also completed my MBA at the University of Geneva.  And when I have time off, I enjoy travelling, skiing, hiking, swimming in the lake and meeting new people.  I've been told by friends who visit how they enjoy spending time in my place - and describe it as being zen, always clean, comfortable, beautiful, inviting and welcoming.  If you are coming for a holiday, my home is an ideal pied-à-terre for sightseeing. If you are here for work and need a place till you find your new home, it's ideally located to get to UN organisations such as the UN, UNHRC, ITU and countless NGOs.  I look foward to meeting you and welcoming you to my home.  Merci et au plaisir!

Borges, Rousseau, Voltaire, Calvin, George Eliot and many many others could be your neighbours some other time in the past.

I am very comfortable sharing apartments, having guest and accommodating different cultures, mentalities and nationalities. neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

neighborhood_overview:
Located at the heart of the city and nestling on the lake shore, Eaux-Vives Cité is a lively and convivial district steeped in history. Eaux-Vives Cité is one of the eight major districts of the City of Geneva. Located at the heart of the city and stretching along the southern shore of Lake Geneva, it borders the districts of Plainpalais Jonction and Champel.

In this district popular with tourists, the inhabitants of Eaux-Vives Cité enjoy an extensive cultural offering including theatres, museums, concert halls and much more. While there is considerable road traffic in Eaux-Vives, this inconvenience is offset by the proximity of the lake and quays, ideal for enjoying a relaxing stroll. The presence of the large parks – Parc des Bastions, Parc des Eaux-Vives and Parc La Grange – as well as several welcoming places and numerous terraces, in particular around the Place du Bourg-de-Four, make the district an ideal place to meet up and make the most of your leisure time.

Residence "Pierres aux Arbres" - apartment "Salève"

This magnificent flat is located in an old farmhouse completely renovated in 2020.

The property, only 2.5 km away from Carouge, is connected with the public transport (10 minutes on foot or 5 by bike): Bus 45 - Pont de Drize; Bus 41 - Milière; Bus 8 - Veyrier Tournettes.

The Léman Express train (Lancy-Bachet stop) is 10 minutes by bike or 5 minutes by car; the motorway, exit Archamps or Etrembières, is also 10 minutes by car.
neighborhood_overview:
The residences "Pierres aux arbres" is the perfect balance between the poetry of the countryside and the comforts of the city.

The view on the Salève as well as the colours of the sun rise and the sunset make this place increbible wonderful and will give you a special remembering of your staying in Geneva.

Troinex is a small and cosy village offering also a grocery shop, a post office and café.

In the neighbourhood you can enjoy walking around among corn and vegetable fields and vineyards.

neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

host_about:
If you can keep your head when all about you;
  Are losing theirs and blaming it on you,
 If you can trust yourself when all men doubt you,
  But make allowance for their doubting too.
 If you can wait and not be tired by waiting,
  Or being lied about, don't deal in lies,
 Or being hated, don't give way to hating,
  And yet don't look too good, nor talk too wise:

 If you can dream—and not make dreams your master;
  If you can think—and not make thoughts your aim;
 If you can meet with Triumph and Disaster,
  And treat those two impostors just the same;
 If you can bear to hear the truth you've spoken
  Twisted by knaves to make a trap for fools,
 Or watch the things you gave your life to, broken,
  And stoop and build 'em up with worn-out tools:

 If you can make a heap of all your winnings
  And risk it on one turn of pitch-and-toss,
 And lose, and start again at your beginnings
  And never breathe a word about your loss;
 If you can force your heart and nerve and sinew
  To serve your turn long after they are gone,
 And so hold on when there is nothing in you
  Except the Will which says to them: "Hold on!"

 If you can talk with crowds and keep your virtue,
  Or walk with Kings—nor lose the common touch,
 If neither foes nor loving friends can hurt you,
  If all men count with you, but none too much;
 If you can fill the unforgiving minute
  With sixty seconds' worth of distance run,
 Yours is the Earth and everything that's in it,
  And—which is more—you'll be a Man, my son!

neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation is ideally located in the Servette district, northeast of Geneva, known for its multicultural and lively atmosphere. There are a wide variety of restaurants, shops and entertainment venues nearby.

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.

The village is a 3-minute walk away, where you'll find a bakery (closed on Monday, Chez Martine on the village square (breakfast from 6am, restaurant at lunchtime and bar in the evening), the Auberge de Jussy restaurant, the town hall (which also doubles as a post office) and a doctor's surgery.

neighborhood_overview:
The Eaux-Vives district is one of the most popular in Geneva for its special atmosphere.
Located on the left bank, it is a stone's throw from the hyper center of Geneva, its famous Rue du Rhone and its low streets which are right next to our pretty old town.
But the Eaux-Vives is on the lakefront, it also offers beautiful walks along the docks with its English garden, its beautiful and iconic flowered clock as well as its water jet and public beaches.
In addition, it has the most beautiful park in the city with stunning views and beautiful sunsets.
This is the recommended area for those who want to discover Geneva from its best angle.
host_about:

neighborhood_overview:

The city of Thônex is located at the border of France and Switzerland, witch offers you a lot of possibilities to go shopping or dining out.
host_about:
Je suis maman de 4 enfants deux filles adultes de 24 et 22 ans et deux garçon de 16 et 14ans. Nous vivons dans notre maison dans un quartier calme proche de la ville. 
Nous louons une chambre au 1er étage de notre maison, que nous pouvons aménager au gré des demandes de nos hôtes, en chambre individuelle, deux lits séparés un grand lit double. Les voyageurs partagent la salle de bain avec baignoire avec mes deux filles.
Mes enfants et moi aimons recevoir et cette chambre est une ouverture sur le monde et d'autres cultures, ce n'est que du positif et un énorme enrichissement.

I am mother of 4 kids aged 24 to 14 , living together in our place.
When we live in the house we have 1 rooms for rent :
A single or double room on the first floor with bathroom to share with children.
We have two dogs and 2 cats. The house is full set with ammenities so that you can spend great  and quite holidays in Switzerland. Close to the Motorway, close to public transportation and close to commercial area.

Soy madre de 4 hijos, que tienen entre 24 y 14 años. Vivimos en una zona muy tranquila muy bien comunicada.
Alquilo una habitacion, está en la primera planta y la puedo preparar como la quieren los huéspedes, simple o doble, a veces incluso pueden dormir 3 personas. Los viajeros comparten el cuarto de baño con mis dos ninos. 
Nos gusta recibir gente y de esta manera abro el horizonte a mis hijos y descubrimos otras culturas en casa, y cada visita es enriquecida.

description:
Modern apartment (one bedroom, one kitchen, one bathroom with bathtub), with beautiful private garden, located in Pregny-Chambésy, 5-10 minutes away from the center of Geneva and International Organisations. Access to the private communal sports center with swimming pool (free of charge) and tennis courts (fee charged), and to a lovely communal private beach located at a 10 minutes walk from the appartement (free of charged).

Finally, 2 bicycles are loaned with the apartment (free of charged),
neighborhood_overview:
The village in which stands the apartment, known as Pregny-Chambésy, is a charming place that is best known for its beautiful nature sites (lake, forests, botanical parcs), while being at direct proximity to the center of the city.

Furthermore, the apartment is located in the area of all the International Organisations (UN, ICRC museum, etc), where cultural activities can take place.

Besides, not less then 4 renowned restaurants are at your disposal in the village : Le Relais de Chambésy (awarded in the Guide Michelin!), L'Auberge des trois coqs, L'Auberge de la Fontaine, Café 9.

The apartments surrounds various places where sporting activities will take place (biking, swimming, tennis, walking, strolling by the lake, mountain climing).

At last, we clearly recommend this apartments for a quality leisure or cultural vacation, or sportive destination.

host_about:
Bonjour ! Je m’appelle Maki, je suis pianiste. Je suis venue du Japon en 2017 à Genève. Mon mari est également musicien professionnel, violoniste.

Normalement nous travaillons notre instrument à la maison pour préparer nos concerts, et voyager ou rencontrer des gens fait partie de nos vies.

Cette chambre et salle de bain privés que nous vous proposons se situent au rez-de-chaussée de la maison, dans un quartier calme qui se développe pour accueillir le nouveau train Léman Express, en circulation à partir de décembre 2019.

Il y a egalement à cet étage une salle de piano, un salon et une cuisine à partager. Si vous le souhaitez vous pouvez avoir accès au piano en demandant « l'offre spéciale ».

Cornavin station is a 34-minute walk from the flat, while Champel station is a 6-minute walk away. The ‘Contamines’ bus stop, just 2 minutes away, makes it easy to get around the city.
Geneva's old town can also be reached on foot in 10 minutes.
Cointrin international airport is 12 minutes by train from Cornavin station and can also be reached by bus.

Things to do/see nearby :
- Stroll along the banks of Lake Geneva
- Visit the old town and St Peter's Cathedral
- Promenade de la Treille
- Parc des Bastions
- English Garden and Flower Clock
- Geneva Botanical Gardens
- Palais des Nations
- Excursions on Lake Geneva

neighborhood_overview:
Jonction is the place where the Rhône and the Arve meet on the west side of Geneva, but it’s also the place where locals meet up in the summer to bask along the water’s edge.

Urban and trendy, Jonction, just 5 minutes from the city centre, is expanding with the creation of pedestrian zones and green spaces.

On the south side of the neighbourhood, the Bois de la Bâtie forest delights kids with its animal park and adults with stunning views, walking and cycling paths.

Jonction is conveniently located only 15 minutes walk from the shores of Lake Geneva along the River Rhône.

On the doorstep is the best of the city - with supermarkets, transport links and restaurants - and the best of nature with the Rhône flowing past and a quiet forest only minutes away.
host_about: British but living in Geneva - clean and tidy - love design, architecture and interesting apartments with loads of character and warmth. Love to travel - experience new places - meet interesting new people.

neighborhood_overview: The place of Bourg-de-Four is a place of the old city of Geneva in Switzerland. Former location of markets and fairs, it is today a tourist place. You will find several examples of 16th century architecture, the fountain that occupies its center and surrounded by shops, restaurants, art galleries, bookshops and upscale boutiques. The biggest church in Geneva, St. Peter's Cathedral, is nearby: a stolen passage, called "Degrees of Chickens", leads in the form of a staircase between and under the buildings.

host_about:
Jean-Philippe:
Je suis français, je suis venu en Suisse pour 2 semaines de vacances et je ne suis jamais reparti depuis plus de 20 ans. J'ai vécu à Genève et aussi à Lausanne. Je suis infirmier de formation, puis je suis devenu cadre de soins. Je me suis ensuite réorienté pour diriger un restaurant à Genève.
Aujourd'hui je donne un nouveau souffle à ma carrière pour les années à venir.
J'aime: les langues étrangères, voyager, les films, la lecture, la cuisine, bien manger, passer des soirées entre amis, faire de nouvelles rencontres, la randonnée.
Je parle français , anglais, espagnol, je me débrouille en allemand et je comprends l'italien.
J'aime cuisiner, donc si vous venez au bon moment, j'ai peut-être un plat en préparation et vous aurez la chance de le partager avec nous.

Xuong:
Je suis vietnamien, je suis arrivé en Suisse en novembre 2012. J'apprends le français, pour le moment je ne travaille pas.
J'aime la cuisine vietnamienne, jouer au tennis sur PS3, le cinéma, la mer, rencontrer du monde, la campagne, sortir avec des amis, voyager.
Je parle vietnamien, anglais, mandarin, cantonais et je commence le français.

Nous avons toujours eu des invités d'un genre ou un autre occupant nos chambres d'amis. Nous aimons avoir des invités. Nous apprécions de passer du temps avec mais ils peuvent aussi mener leur petite vie dans leur coin, comme nous avons aussi parfois besoin de tranquillité.

Nous sommes heureux de pouvoir recevoir des gens des quatre coins du monde et de partager et échanger avec eux. Nous tenterons de leur faire découvrir la vie en Suisse et les bonnes combines que nous connaissons pour profiter au mieux de notre ville.

GLBT bienvenus

Jean-Philippe:
I am French, I came to Switzerland for 2 weeks vacation and I never left for nearly 20 years. I lived in Geneva and also in Lausanne. I am a nurse, and I became nurse manager. I then shifted to run a restaurant in Geneva.
Today I give a new life to my career for years to come.
Likes: foreign languages, traveling, movies, reading, cooking, eat well, spend evenings with friends, meet new people, hiking.
I speak French, English, Spanish, German I'm doing and I understand Italian.

I love to cook, so if you come at the right time, I may have been baking and you'll get to share with a cup of tea or coffee or vietnamese coffee.

Xuong:
I am Vietnamese, I arrived in Switzerland in November 2012. I'm learning French at the moment I'm not working.
I love Vietnamese food, play tennis on PS3, cinema, sea, meet people, the countryside, out with friends, traveling.
I speak Vietnamese, English, Mandarin, Cantonese and I started the French.

We've had guests of one kind or another occupying my spare rooms for most of life - I enjoy having guests, and love to entertain, but we can appreciate giving people their own quiet space as we also need our own privacy.
We are happy to hear from people around the world to share and exchange with them. We try to introduce them to life in Switzerland.

GLBT Friendly

name: 73 Chambre Cornavin Genève
neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation is ideally located in the Servette district, northeast of Geneva, known for its multicultural and lively atmosphere. There are a wide variety of restaurants, shops and entertainment venues nearby.

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.

The residence is located in Collex-Bossy, a peaceful village offering a pleasant living environment, around 20 minutes' drive from Geneva. The ‘Collex , École’ bus stop is a 2-minute walk away, taking you to Geneva city centre in 30 minutes.

There are several restaurants in the village of Collex-Bossy. Supermarkets and other amenities can be found in neighbouring Versoix.

Cointrin international airport can be reached in 10 minutes by car or 30 minutes by public transport.

Things to see and do

- Bellevue or Versoix beaches
- Hiking in the Foretaille and Les Douves nature reserves
- Walking along the banks of Lake Geneva and the Jet d'eau
- Geneva Botanical Garden
- Palais des Nations
- Excursions on Lake Geneva

description:

If you need to have an official address in Geneva, if an official domiciliation is required by your employer for example, it is possible, but a special contract must be signed. This official address is not included in nocarz contract.
host_about: Passionate about Geneva’s history, I like to tell stories for a good understanding of Geneva, an International City of only 199’000 inhabitants. The farmhouse was built in 1712, the very same year Jean-Jacques Rousseau, who was a philosopher, musician, botanist and novelist, was also born in Geneva. Apart from taking care of the guests, the house, the garden and the animals (cats, dog, hens), I am an entrepreneur and author. I write books on collaborative management, creativity, heutagogy and collective intelligence. My companion Cristobal is a “grand format” portrait’s painter. His studio is also located in the farmhouse. Our values : support, pleasure, integrity, creativity, listening, autonomy.

name: 612 Studio Centre-ville Cornavin
neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

neighborhood_overview:
Staying in Eaux-Vives means living in the heart of the city and still being able to enjoy the refreshing quietness of the lake shore.

Behind Quai Gustave Ador and its 19th century style buildings, you'll discover a bustling and vibrant area. Countless stores and restaurants serve cuisine from all over the world. The atmosphere is friendly and relaxed.

On the Eastern part of the district lie two of Geneva's largest parks: the Parc des Eaux-Vives and the Parc La Grange. Both are great for families, couples and sports enthusiasts in all seasons and weathers.

People living in Eaux-Vives are usually young professionals or couples. There are also families living there. It is lively without being noisy

You have all the main shops & businesses around the corner, it is in the middle of the city so easy access to any part of the city. Close to the charming Old Town / Vielle Ville

neighborhood_overview: Plainpalais Jonction is one of the eight major districts of the City of Geneva. The area is bordered by two rivers, the Rhone and the Arve, which converge at the tip of the appropriately named ‘Jonction’ sector. Plainpalais Jonction is a dynamic district bursting with restaurants, bars, cafés and shops of all kinds. The numerous theatres and cultural venues contribute to the vitality of the district. Its specialist shops, numerous academic institutions and its proximity to the hospital attract far more people than those merely living in the district... which does not for all that prevent the latter from playing an active role in associative life and the life of the district in general.

name: 00B Studio centre-ville GENÈVE
neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

neighborhood_overview:
Lucia's home is located in Geneva, Switzerland.

This gorgeous apartment enjoys a privileged location in the neuralgic point to move easily in the four cardinal points, where easily move all over all the city and surroundings thanks to the great public transportation close by.

You will find it ideal for touring Geneva by walking, since you have everything close by, restaurants, convenient shops 7/7, 3 supermarkets, medical center downstairs, Gym right in the corner, department stores, tram stop just 3 mins. away, Lake 15 minutes walking, the old town of Geneva just next to the lake and other attractions very accessible.

* Airport just 10 mins. away

* Mall Balexert just 3 minutes by tramway.

*United Nations with a direct bus that takes you there in 6 minutes, though it is easy to do by walking

* The commercial center of Geneva, where you can enjoy the most recognized touristic attractions, shopping, etc. approx. 15 minute

neighborhood_overview:
Chambésy is a picturesque neighborhood located in the canton of Geneva, Switzerland. It is situated on the western outskirts of the city of Geneva and is known for its tranquil and idyllic setting. Chambésy is part of the larger municipality of Pregny-Chambésy, which encompasses several other neighbouring villages.

One of the defining features of Chambésy is its lush green landscapes and beautiful parks. The area is surrounded by expansive gardens, sprawling vineyards, and dense forests, creating a serene and natural ambiance. The nearby Lake Geneva adds to the scenic beauty, providing stunning views and recreational opportunities.

neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

neighborhood_overview:
The farmhouse is ideally located in Servette/Petit Saconnex district, on the straight road from the train station to the airport.
In the area La Servette, you find all opportunities for grocery (Migros, Coop, Denner, Aldi) and for laundry (just before Migros or just after), and also Hair dresser, Backery, La Poste, etc.

host_about: Passionate about Geneva’s history, I like to tell stories for a good understanding of Geneva, an International City of only 199’000 inhabitants. The farmhouse was built in 1712, the very same year Jean-Jacques Rousseau, who was a philosopher, musician, botanist and novelist, was also born in Geneva. Apart from taking care of the guests, the house, the garden and the animals (cats, dog, hens), I am an entrepreneur and author. I write books on collaborative management, creativity, heutagogy and collective intelligence. My companion Cristobal is a “grand format” portrait’s painter. His studio is also located in the farmhouse. Our values : support, pleasure, integrity, creativity, listening, autonomy.

I am looking forward to be your host.

Regards,

Anjo

neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

- Tavel House: The oldest private building in Geneva, transformed into a museum of urban history and daily life in Geneva.

neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

host_about:
Jean-Philippe:
Je suis français, je suis venu en Suisse pour 2 semaines de vacances et je ne suis jamais reparti depuis plus de 20 ans. J'ai vécu à Genève et aussi à Lausanne. Je suis infirmier de formation, puis je suis devenu cadre de soins. Je me suis ensuite réorienté pour diriger un restaurant à Genève.
Aujourd'hui je donne un nouveau souffle à ma carrière pour les années à venir.
J'aime: les langues étrangères, voyager, les films, la lecture, la cuisine, bien manger, passer des soirées entre amis, faire de nouvelles rencontres, la randonnée.
Je parle français , anglais, espagnol, je me débrouille en allemand et je comprends l'italien.
J'aime cuisiner, donc si vous venez au bon moment, j'ai peut-être un plat en préparation et vous aurez la chance de le partager avec nous.

Xuong:
Je suis vietnamien, je suis arrivé en Suisse en novembre 2012. J'apprends le français, pour le moment je ne travaille pas.
J'aime la cuisine vietnamienne, jouer au tennis sur PS3, le cinéma, la mer, rencontrer du monde, la campagne, sortir avec des amis, voyager.
Je parle vietnamien, anglais, mandarin, cantonais et je commence le français.

Nous avons toujours eu des invités d'un genre ou un autre occupant nos chambres d'amis. Nous aimons avoir des invités. Nous apprécions de passer du temps avec mais ils peuvent aussi mener leur petite vie dans leur coin, comme nous avons aussi parfois besoin de tranquillité.

Nous sommes heureux de pouvoir recevoir des gens des quatre coins du monde et de partager et échanger avec eux. Nous tenterons de leur faire découvrir la vie en Suisse et les bonnes combines que nous connaissons pour profiter au mieux de notre ville.

GLBT bienvenus

Jean-Philippe:
I am French, I came to Switzerland for 2 weeks vacation and I never left for nearly 20 years. I lived in Geneva and also in Lausanne. I am a nurse, and I became nurse manager. I then shifted to run a restaurant in Geneva.
Today I give a new life to my career for years to come.
Likes: foreign languages, traveling, movies, reading, cooking, eat well, spend evenings with friends, meet new people, hiking.
I speak French, English, Spanish, German I'm doing and I understand Italian.

I love to cook, so if you come at the right time, I may have been baking and you'll get to share with a cup of tea or coffee or vietnamese coffee.

I am Vietnamese, I arrived in Switzerland in November 2012. I'm learning French at the moment I'm not working.
I love Vietnamese food, play tennis on PS3, cinema, sea, meet people, the countryside, out with friends, traveling.
I speak Vietnamese, English, Mandarin, Cantonese and I started the French.

We've had guests of one kind or another occupying my spare rooms for most of life - I enjoy having guests, and love to entertain, but we can appreciate giving people their own quiet space as we also need our own privacy.
We are happy to hear from people around the world to share and exchange with them. We try to introduce them to life in Switzerland.

name: Charmante Maison de ville
description: In Geneva, in the heart of the Carouge district in the former space of the theater of the same name, the interior design office and showroom “DIMANCHE” has just finished its guest house. Or rather that of Madame K., a cultured, whimsical and above all fantasized woman who served as a model for this charming town house. There you will find a spacious eat-in kitchen, a living room, two double bedrooms and a single bedroom (convertible into a double) as well as two bathrooms.
neighborhood_overview:
Historic district of Geneva. According to Wikipedia: “Carouge has been part of the Republic and Canton of Geneva since 1816. It is famous for the “old Carouge” district, which retains a certain charm and where the terraces of the bistros are frequented when the sunny days return” But… Before 1816? Ho ho ho! According to the other tourist site, rts: “Nicknamed the Sardinian city, the territory was ceded to the Kingdom of Sardinia by the Republic of Geneva during the Treaty of Turin in 1754. Under the will of King Victor-Amadeus III of Sardinia, the hamlet is built in town by Piedmontese architects who give it its character. In 1786, the king granted it the title of Royal City. The commune has been united in Geneva since the Treaty of Turin of 1816." More detailed information also on the official Carouge website

neighborhood_overview:
Russin is a perfect starting point for a comfortable and varied stay, for discovering the city of Geneva, for hiking, for wine tours and for visiting the Geneva international Motor Show.

In Russin there is a very small grocery shop with a bakery, a coffee shop and a restaurant.

There is a train from Russin station to Geneva every 30 minutes. The journey takes 15 minutes. The train station Russin is 5 minutes walk from the apartment.
14 minutes by car from the Balexert Congress Centre and 12 minutes from Geneva Airport. 16 minutes to the Palexpo

name: Calm spacious renovated unit, garden and parking
description:
My unit is a large suite (40 sqm) attached to our house, but independent. You will receive a set of keys and come and go as you wish.

Our place is located in a quiet residencial area close to beautiful Carouge and its market. The city center is easily accessible by bus and tramway. See Getting around section for more information.

The bus stop is 2' walking distance, aprox 150m.
neighborhood_overview:
A bakery and tea room serves fresh croissants, bread, sandwiches and is only 3 to 5 minutes walk. The place also serves salads and pizzas at noon and in the evenings.

There is as well a convenience store at walking distance (indications are in the information book in the unit).

A big shopping center with restaurants, shopping, supermarket and cinemas is 1.4km away, reachable also by bus in 7', or by car in 10'. The shopping center provides a cheap delivery service with electrical bycicles right to the house door. You can take advantage of it! I will explain to you how it works, it is very easy, and I use it all the time.

We can lend one bicycle to you from our household, if you like.

Very large choice of good restaurants in close Carouge and Geneva. I will make recommendations for you.

The unit is 2 minutes walk from bus stop. It takes approximately 10 minutes ride to Carouge, 18 minutes ride to town center.

Welcome!!
host_about:
I see myself -and I hope that I live up to it- as a progressist humanist. 
My life is fuller when I can host and exchange with people from around the world, in every country, ethnicity,religion, sexual orientation. I cherish the diversity.
I couldn't live without: books, food and wine, nature, music, love. And, when possible, baths in the cold sea!

Welcome to Geneva and welcome to Menorca!

neighborhood_overview:
You have the best of Geneva walking distance!! Lake 3 min away.
Best of international cuisine starting from Da Paolo (Italian), al dar (Lebanese) to the chique and very trendy peruvian Alma.
For drinks Yvette de marseille, bottle brothers and all the bars in the street are always full and well known. Gym is 50 meters away next to migros the supermarket. Cinema is also 50 meters away. The area is the most well served, hip and trendy of all of Geneva.
host_about:
Friendly and outgoing, I establish relationships for a living, therefore also very respectful of other's space and time. 
Love adventure travelling, so if I am approaching you it is probably because im either in a scuba diving spree, sailing frenzy or both.  Yah i like good weather... and food, especially food. So tell me your favorite no frills restaurant in the area, I'll make sure to go try it, no matter the cuisine.
Originally Italian lived all over the globe and now settled in Switzerland.

description: Spacious studio with washer/dryer, Wi-fi, supermarket and gym in the same building, cleaner + ironing, cable HDTV, everything you need! Great public transport to UN, IO's, bus stop on your doorstep and the lake just a stone's throw away.
neighborhood_overview: This is the most sought after area in Geneva: the lake is practically on your doorstep, with a boat taxi (2chf/ride) taking you to the other side of the lake. You can run or roll along the promenade; there's a free bike rental offered by the city a stone's throw from the flat, by the Jardin Anglais. Chill out in the Bodega Tapas Bar across the street, or go for Cocktails at the nearby l'Atelier. The following morning, have a vegetarian brunch at Clou de Giraffe or Pain Quotidien. Two much loved restaurants, Da Paolo and L'esquisse, are on the same street. I guarantee you won't be thirsty or hungry in this neighbourhood!

neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

neighborhood_overview:
Saint-Gervais neighborhood is located in Geneva Historic Center, close to Old Town and Rhone. It is charming and lively, known for its cobblestone streets, historic buildings and bohemian vibe.

The neighborhood is home to many cafes, bars and restaurants, as well as independent shops and art galleries. The Place du Bourg-de-Four, located a short walk away, is one of the nerve centers of the social and cultural life of Geneva, where cafes, restaurants, bookstores and shops meet.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also known for its weekly market, where locals come to buy fresh, local produce. It is also famous for its church of the same name, which dates from the 15th century and is considered one of the most beautiful examples of Gothic architecture in Geneva.

The Saint-Gervais neighborhood is also very convenient for guests, as it is located next to Cornavin train station.

In addition, the neighborhood is very well connected by public transp

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.

neighborhood_overview:
The Eaux-Vives area in Geneva is a vibrant and lively neighborhood located on the southern shore of Lake Geneva. It is known for its charming streets, beautiful parks, and proximity to the city center (5-10min walk). Eaux-Vives offers a mix of residential and commercial spaces, with numerous shops, restaurants, bars and cafes lining the streets.

One of the main attractions in the area is the Parc La Grange, a stunning public park with a magnificent rose garden, historic mansion, and breathtaking lake views. The park is a popular spot for picnics, strolls, and outdoor concerts during the summer months.

name: Stellar Stay in Wonderful Old Town
description:
This great little apartment has been furnished to an impeccable standard.

It’s the ideal retreat for a fully facilitated & up-scale stay, located in the absolute heart of Geneva. We believe it’s the ultimate location to experience the city center the way it should be.

At 70 m from St. Pierre Cathedral and 800 m from Jet d'Eau, the flat is the heart of Geneva's old town. Get ready to get inspired! All in all, guaranteed enjoyment and relaxation. Settle in a professionally cleaned home.
neighborhood_overview:
You’ve probably heard all the stereotypes about Geneva. But it’s only when you come that they can be challenged. Yes, there’s wealth, fondue, chocolate and watchmaking. But Geneva is also charged with diversity and creativity, in neighbourhoods like Les Grottes or the Italian-flavoured Carouge. Get the Geneva Pass for free access to museums, several tours, cruises and transportation!

Lake Geneva and its iconic plume of water will draw your eye on promenades and lush waterside parks, while Mont Salève is a slice of the Alps in the background. Geneva is still a beacon of diplomacy, where organizations like the United Nations and the Red Cross convene. Loads to do for all tastes, from outdoor adventures for local explorers to total isolation for those who prefer the homely and the comfy!

Geneva's Old Town, in French called Vieille Ville, is an ancient maze of small streets and picturesque squares, filled with homey cafés, restaurants, galleries, museums and historica
host_about:
Hi!
My name is Augustin. I’m a 31-year-old entrepreneur with a passion for hospitality and travel, always looking to create amazing guest experiences. I really enjoy the ability to share the experience of living in this great home. 

Definitely check with me for amazing sunset locations, where to go for superb walks, and where to have mindblowing culinary experiences! 

I have lived in Switzerland, Paris, Shanghai and Panama, and Medellin, Colombia for work and love to discover new cultures and landscapes myself.

Whether I’m cycling 5000km trails, climbing for 2 months in a fjord far away in Greenland, or freediving down to 35m deep, adventure and I are friends, to say the least!

I will always try to meet your expectations and even go beyond the expectation of your stay. If you have any suggestions for me, please let me know!

Some great features I have are due to the inspirations of other guests that stayed with me and had interesting ideas. So please don't hesitate to let me know your thoughts. 

Feel free to communicate with me!

Hope to see you soon,

Augustin

description:

name: Unique & Tasteful Apartment
description:
This beautifully designed 1-bedroom apartment offers a perfect blend of style and functionality. Thoughtfully furnished and carefully curated, every detail has been considered to create a warm and inviting space.

The apartment features one spacious bedrooms and one full bathroom, providing comfort and convenience for daily living. The living room, with its adaptable layout, can be easily converted into an additional bedroom.

Ideal for anyone seeking a unique and elegant home
neighborhood_overview:
Located in the heart of Geneva, this apartment benefits from a prime location in a vibrant and sought-after neighborhood. Known for its centrality and charm, the area offers a mix of bustling city life and serene spaces to unwind.

Just steps away, you’ll find a variety of shops, boutiques, and local cafes, perfect for enjoying the city’s lively atmosphere. The neighborhood is also home to excellent dining options, ranging from cozy bistros to fine restaurants.

For those who value connectivity, the area is exceptionally well-served by public transportation, making it easy to explore Geneva and beyond. Parks and green spaces are also nearby, offering opportunities for relaxation and recreation.

This neighborhood combines convenience, culture, and an inviting community spirit, making it a fantastic place to call home.

name: Cosy boat in the heart of GVA
description:
If you would like an outdoorsy lake experience in the middle of the city under the symbol of Geneva, then this is the place for you. Our boat offers a fantastic view and a unique sleeping experience - you will be lulled to sleep by the gentle rocking of the boat on the waves. During the day, sit above deck and enjoy the refreshing breeze from the Jet d’Eau. The boat offers basic camping amenities and, thanks to its central location, you can find everything else you might want within 500m.
Enjoy!

The city center is 10 minutes away, with shops and transport are right next door.

Local public transport (Train and bus) and shops nearby.
host_about:
I am an organized and clean lady, a mother of two kids, who loves to travel and appreciates spending my holidays in apartments instead of hotels. I love to cook even on my holidays and enjoy having more space than a hotel room offers.

My sweet apartment has everything you need to feel at home.

description:
This very quiet and bright studio flat is in one of the best locations in town. It is right by the lake and close to a range of great restaurants, bars and shops.

The United Nations are a 10 minute walk away, and the train station a 7 minute walk.

It is right by the wonderful Quai Wilson, one the most gorgeous lakeside promenades.

The studio gives you the best location, in the heart of everything while still being quiet and peaceful. For a studio flat it is very spacious.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is one of the nicest you will find in Geneva. Right by the beautiful lake-side promenade, it has many good restaurants and bars. The park is a few minutes walk away as are the United Nations and the train stations.

Quai Wilson, the nicest of the Geneva lakeside promenades is right outside.

neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation is ideally located in the Servette district, northeast of Geneva, known for its multicultural and lively atmosphere. There are a wide variety of restaurants, shops and entertainment venues nearby.

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.

The accommodation is ideally located in the Servette district, northeast of Geneva, known for its multicultural and lively atmosphere. There are a wide variety of restaurants, shops and entertainment venues nearby.

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.

description:
Nice and comfortable bedroom in farmhouse from the 18th century. It comfortably fits one and is centrally located in the hearth of Geneva while enjoying nice woods and calm. Enjoy a nice kitchen, access to the garden and easy access to all bus lines.

The 5 rooms have been on nocarz since 2015. Due to a change of account, all the history of comments is unfortunately lost, but can be found photographed at the end of the diashow of the accommodation with an excellent rate of 4.5 to 5 stars!
host_about: Passionate about Geneva’s history, I like to tell stories for a good understanding of Geneva, an International City of only 199’000 inhabitants. The farmhouse was built in 1712, the very same year Jean-Jacques Rousseau, who was a philosopher, musician, botanist and novelist, was also born in Geneva. Apart from taking care of the guests, the house, the garden and the animals (cats, dog, hens), I am an entrepreneur and author. I write books on collaborative management, creativity, heutagogy and collective intelligence. My companion Cristobal is a “grand format” portrait’s painter. His studio is also located in the farmhouse. Our values : support, pleasure, integrity, creativity, listening, autonomy.

neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation is ideally located in the Servette district, northeast of Geneva, known for its multicultural and lively atmosphere. There are a wide variety of restaurants, shops and entertainment venues nearby.

The neighborhood is easily accessible by public transport, with multiple tram and bus stops a short walk away. The POTTERY stop is right next to the accommodation, making it easy for you to get around the city. If you want to get to CERN, it will take about 20 minutes by tram, while the airport is accessible in about 20 minutes by public transit.

By staying in the Servette neighborhood, you can easily explore the local life of Geneva and immerse yourself in its multicultural and lively culture. And thanks to the proximity to Geneva - Cornavin Station, you can easily discover other cities in Switzerland and international destinations. The Servette neighborhood is therefore a great choice for your stay in Geneva.
host_about: J'aime offrir une expérience de séjour personnalisée et authentique. Je partage mes connaissances locales pour aider les voyageurs à découvrir la ville comme un local. Mon objectif est de faire en sorte que mes voyageurs se sentent chez eux à Genève, en leur offrant un accueil chaleureux et toutes les informations pour un séjour inoubliable.

neighborhood_overview:
Servette is the neighborhood in the heart of Geneva. Its central location and public transport options, makes it easy to navigate between lake, river, old town and mountains. The authentic neighborhood has various parks and a lot of charmy restaurants ("Grottes"). It is only 10 minutes walk from the main station, from Nations (international organizations), the Rhône and 20 minutes walk from the lake. Public transport is very easy (train station, tram 18 and 14, bus options...).

In the street of the apartment, there are several supermarkets, a pharmacy, the bank and also some cosy authentic bars!

Happily share more insights and tips with you once you arrive!
